# Customization Guide

## Theme Customization

### Colors

Edit CSS variables in `quartz/styles/custom.scss`:

```scss
:root {
  --primary-dark: #092045;      // Main color
  --primary-medium: #1A3A6B;   // Links
  --primary-light: #2E5491;    // Hover states
}
```

### Typography

Update fonts in `quartz.config.ts`:

```typescript
theme: {
  typography: {
    header: "Your Header Font",
    body: "Your Body Font",
    code: "Your Code Font",
  },
}
```

### Spacing

Adjust layout spacing:

```scss
:root {
  --layout-inline: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
}
```

## Content Structure

### Homepage

Edit `content/index.md` for homepage content.

### Navigation

Update navigation links in `quartz.layout.ts`:

```typescript
footer: Component.Footer({
  links: {
    "Your Site": "https://yourdomain.com",
    "GitHub": "https://github.com/your-org/your-repo",
  },
}),
```

### Content Organization

Organize content in `content/` directory:

```
content/
├── index.md          # Homepage
├── about.md          # About page
├── blog/             # Blog posts
└── docs/              # Documentation
```

## Component Customization

### Custom Components

Create custom components in `quartz/components/`:

```typescript
import { QuartzComponent, QuartzComponentConstructor } from "./types"

const MyComponent: QuartzComponent = ({ displayClass }) => {
  return <div class={displayClass}>My Component</div>
}

MyComponent.css = `
.my-component {
  /* styles */
}
`

export default (() => MyComponent) satisfies QuartzComponentConstructor
```

### Override Existing Components

Copy component from `quartz/components/` and modify:

1. Copy component file
2. Modify as needed
3. Component will override default

## Configuration Options

### Site Metadata

In `quartz.config.ts`:

```typescript
configuration: {
  pageTitle: "Your Site Name",
  baseUrl: "yourdomain.com",
  locale: "en-US",
}
```

### Plugins

Enable/disable plugins in `quartz.config.ts`:

```typescript
plugins: {
  transformers: [
    // Add or remove transformers
  ],
  filters: [
    // Add or remove filters
  ],
  emitters: [
    // Add or remove emitters
  ],
}
```

## Deployment Customization

### GitHub Pages

Configure in `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`:

```yaml
env:
  BASE_URL: yourdomain.com
```

### Custom Domain

Add `CNAME` file in `quartz/static/`:

```
yourdomain.com
```

## Best Practices

1. **Use CSS Variables**: Makes theming easier
2. **Keep Customizations Documented**: Note changes in README
3. **Test Responsively**: Check mobile and desktop
4. **Version Control**: Commit customization changes
5. **Sync Regularly**: Keep upstream changes in sync

